<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="571" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d571">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1230: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-24T18:00:00-04:00">June 24, 1931—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>45. Your 38, June 23, 2 p.m. Bolivia has formally and categorically
                            refused to consider the question of double arbitration. The Department
                            does not consider it advisable to make such a proposal as it would most
                            surely be rejected and would very likely prevent a serious discussion by
                            Bolivia of the settlement of the Chaco dispute.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
